List of things to do after a fresh installation of Fedora 26-27

###	Edit /etc/sudoers file to grant sudo credentials to regular users
	su
	visudo

### Edit Selinux settings to disable it
	vi /etc/selinux/config
	SELINUX=enforcing	==>		SELINUX=disabled

### Configure profiles for gnome-terminal
	No showing menu bar by default
    Rename original Profile
        unamed      ==>     Default
    Clone the default profile to create a new one "Gray"
    Profile "Gray"
		General
			Font fira mono regular 10
			115 columns x 25 rows
			Rewrap on resize actived
		Colors
			Default color white on gray #404040
			Bold color active
			Cursor color white on red 3
			Highlight color orange 2 on blue 3
			Built-in schema Tango
		Scrolling
			Unlimit scrollback

###	Configure GEdit
	View
		Display line numbers
		Display right margin at column (80)
		Display statusbar
		Highlight current line
		Highlight matching brackets
	Editor
		Tab with (4)
		Enable automatic indentation
		Autosave files every (10) minutes
	Fonts and Colors
		Font monospace regular 10
		Oblivion theme

### Add shortcuts to keyboard
	Terminal		Win + T
	Firefox			Alt + F
	Google-Chrome	Alt + C
	GEdit			Alt + G

### Run script "Fedora_26_27_Configuration_Update"

### Run script "Fedora_26_27_Apps_Installation"

### Copy .bashrc for both, user and root, from backups

### Copy .git files from a backup to user's home

### Install vim
	dnf install vim

### If installing a Virtual machine
    Insert and run Guest Additions Disk and reboot

### Manually, install, if needed:
    LibreOffice
    Ffmpeg from git, following the script:
        "Install_Ffmpeg_from_Git"
    Install Video editor "Lightworks"
